{"text":"Digging this song. If any of you ever even tried to produce and make a rap song, you would understand that making something like this takes time, effort, and is harder than it looks. Rap is a form of art, and art is something you can't do right or wrong. If you don't like it, then it's all good. If you do, more power to you. You can't compare this style of rap with Kendrick's because if you were to put Kendrick on a mainstream song, he would sound bad. (If you don't believe me, listen to Fuckin' Problems and his verse is just something that isn't Kendrick.) Just appreciate what this guy is doing, and that is showing that he can do different styles of rap whether it be straight lyrical chill shit to this banger type flow.
